FBIS4-1020 "drafr075_c_94029" FBIS-AFR-94-075 Daily Report 18 Apr 1994 REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA IFP Youth Brigade Postpones Plans for Strike IFP Youth Brigade Postpones Plans for Strike MB1804164294 Johannesburg SAPA in English 1632 GMT 18 Apr 94 MB1804164294 Johannesburg SAPA English BFN [Report by A. Thomson] [Text] Johannesburg April 18 SAPA -- The Inkatha Freedom Party [IFP] Youth Brigade on Monday [18 April] evening announced it had postponed plans for a stayaway in the Johannesburg area on Tuesday, after talks with the South African Council of Business [name as received]. Spokesman for the brigade's PWV [Pretoria, Witwatersrand, Vereeniging] branch, Mr Carter Ndlovu, told SAPA by telephone talks with SA Chamber of Business [SACOB] in Johannesburg on Monday had been "fruitful and constructive". SACOB delegates had expressed concern about the effect of the stayaway on business. Mr Ndlovu said the talks were continuing and a further statement would be made later.
